## Learning Objective Format
Every lesson pack opens with a LO slide using this format:
```
LEARNING OBJECTIVES
By the end of this lesson you will be able to:
LO1 — [Action verb + specific capability] (Knowledge / Application / Analysis)
LO2 — ...
LO3 — ...

ASSESSMENT: [Knowledge check / Syndicate exercise / Tabletop scenario]
```
Bloom's taxonomy levels: Remember → Understand → Apply → Analyse → Evaluate → Create
Day 1 packs: mostly Remember + Understand
Day 2 packs: Understand + Apply
Day 3 packs: Apply + Analyse + Evaluate

## Workbook Format (4 books, PDF)

### Structure per workbook
```
Cover page (classification banner, day/module title, SPECTRAL PCM logo)
Daily timetable
─── Lesson N ───────────────────────────────
Lesson title + LOs (1 page)
Key concepts (2–4 pages — not a copy of the slides, adds depth)
Worked examples / case study extract (1–2 pages)
Knowledge check — 10 MCQ + 2 short-answer (1 page)
Exercise brief (for syndicate/tabletop) (1 page)
Space for notes (1 page per lesson)
─────────────────────────────────────────────
Day summary — 5 key takeaways
Glossary for the day
Reference list
```

### Knowledge Check Answer Format
MCQ: A / B / C / D — single best answer
Pass threshold: 80% for knowledge checks (not final assessment)
Answers in instructor version only — not in student workbook

## Assessment
- End of Day 3: written knowledge assessment — 50 MCQ, 3 short-answer, 75 min
- Pass mark: 80% (40/50 MCQ + satisfactory short-answer responses)
- Assessed by: course instructor (SPECTRAL PCM-certified)
- Certificate: SPECTRAL PCM Course Completion

## Slide Count Rules
- Maximum 24 slides per 50-min lesson pack (including title + LO + summary = 3 structural slides, leaving 21 for content)
- Every slide needs a visual — no text-only slides
- If content exceeds 21 slides, split into Part A / Part B (two packs)
- Charts/tables count as visuals
- Higgsfield placeholders count as visuals

## Higgsfield Prompt Delivery
One batch per pack, delivered as a markdown file named `[PACKCODE]_higgsfield_prompts.md` in the same directory as the slide build script. Format:
```markdown
## [PACK CODE] — [Pack Title]
### Slide [N] — [Slide Title]
**Purpose:** [what the image should communicate]
**Style:** cinematic military documentary, desaturated, [warm/cool] grading, golden hour / NVG-blue
**Subject:** [specific subject with operational context — aircraft type, terrain, action]
**Mood:** tense / professional / operational
**Aspect:** 16:9
**Negative:** cartoon, low quality, watermark, civilian aesthetic, cheerful, text
```
